cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on optimizing the quality of experience for video streaming applications, which involves efficient management of heterogeneous cloud resources. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video streaming applications and proposes a model for describing a system architecture for such applications. This falls under the domain of multimedia. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the allocation of CDN for a video request and central storage and bandwidth allocation, which are related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel algorithm to solve the formulated optimization problem, which involves control and optimization of the system. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes an algorithm to minimize the stall duration tail probability (SDTP) metric, which involves data structures and algorithms.
